episode: When my daughter and I went to Las Vegas.

dialogue.speaker: Human
dialogue.message: I was excited when my daughter and I visited Las Vegas in September.

dialogue.speaker: Bot
dialogue.message: That sounds like a blast! What did you guys do there?

dialogue.speaker: Human
dialogue.message: We seen the Sphere.

dialogue.speaker: Bot
dialogue.message: How was it? Was it as cool as you expected?

dialogue.speaker: Human
dialogue.message: It was very cool. It has the most detailed high definition image I have ever seen.

dialogue.speaker: Bot
dialogue.message: Wow, that sounds amazing!

dialogue.speaker: Human
dialogue.message: We also went to a Cirque du Soleil show.

dialogue.speaker: Bot
dialogue.message: Awesome! Which one did you see?

dialogue.speaker: Human
dialogue.message: It was called New York New York.

dialogue.speaker: Bot
dialogue.message: That's a great one! Did your daughter love it?

dialogue.speaker: Human
dialogue.message: She did. We had seats in the front row.

dialogue.speaker: Bot
dialogue.message: That's awesome! You must've felt like you were part of the show!

dialogue.speaker: Human
dialogue.message: We were a part of the show. I had to make a basket into a basketball hoop during the show since we were right there.

dialogue.speaker: Bot
dialogue.message: That's hilarious! What was that like?

dialogue.speaker: Human
dialogue.message: It was very cool. We also visited Hoover Dam while we were there.

dialogue.speaker: Bot
dialogue.message: Classic Vegas trip! How was the dam tour?

dialogue.speaker: Human
dialogue.message: It was fine, but it's just a big dam. We could have also went to the Grand Canyon but The time on a bus was too long.

dialogue.speaker: Bot
dialogue.message: Yeah, the bus ride to the Grand Canyon can be a long haul.

dialogue.speaker: Human
dialogue.message: I think they said we would be on a bus for 12 or more hours.

dialogue.speaker: Bot
dialogue.message: That's a whole day! No wonder you passed on it.
